data.description: Ready for its next chapter! Home appraised twice at $500K in 2020. Since then, NEW roof, NEW roof deck with WOW views!, HVAC 2021, and entire exterior wall repointed. Picture a delightful life here in the timeless elegance of this magnificent home. A turn-of-the-century gem, this dwelling presents an ideal blend of historical charm and modern functionality. With a well flowing layout and abundant space, enjoyment of private respite as well as the company of kith and kin can be held with ease. The list of desirable city home amenities to enhance home life here is long, including off-street parking, a rooftop deck offering stunning city views, an abundance of natural light, classic Baltimore exposed brick, and ample storage spread across four beautifully finished levels. The entry vestibule adorned with a stained glass transom is just the first note of a symphony of historic details lovingly preserved throughout the home. Hardwood floors, original staircases, intricate trim, fireplaces, and mantels all whisper stories of bygone eras. A cozy yet radiant living room fronts the home sitting off the entry hall and a generous greeting space. A convenient and well placed half bath is passed on the way to the large kitchen, featuring all the modern conveniences we've come to expect. Create culinary masterpieces on the impressive 6-burner gas range, under a coffered tin style ceiling, steeped in historic charm. The kitchen flows effortlessly into a spacious dining room, providing ample space for cherished moments breaking bread with family and friends. Step outside to a wrought iron and brick enclosed patio ahead of the parking pad. Back inside an open staircase with middle landing leads you to the finished lower level accented with rustic exposed beams. This space offers plenty of flexibility for use with two rooms that can serve a multitude of purposes. Closet and unfinished space for storage allows the rest of the level to actually be living space. A full bathroom here ensures functionality and provides an opportunity as a guest area or additional quarters for permanent residents. Heading back up, ascend the grand original staircase to the upper levels where you can retire for rest and rejuvenation in one of three spacious bedrooms. The first upper level boasts a front bedroom with a large walk-in closet, lofty ceilings, and abundant natural light streaming through three tall, charmingly trimmed windows. The rear bedroom features an attached full bathroom and enjoys its own infusion of natural light through two large windows on the side. On to the uppermost level, you'll discover the primary suite. The en suite bathroom indulges with a soaking tub and separate stand-up shower, adorned with modern yet classically styled floor tiles, in harmony with the rest of the bathrooms on these upper levels. At the back the office or bonus room provides space for productivity, be it work or hobby. Admire the skyline and neighborhood around from the newly rebuilt two-tier deck accessed via a wet bar area creating a seamless outdoor retreat. Your daily routines are effortlessly facilitated with dedicated off-street parking and easy access to commuter routes, putting the charm of Charm City and beyond at your doorstep. This home has been cherished for a century and quarter more, bridging the 19th to the 21st! Come and experience the true essence of urban living as part of the history and future of Baltimore. Don't let this opportunity pass you by. Schedule your tour today!
